Lieutenant Commader '''Tom Riefesel''' is an officer in the [[Royal Canadian Navy]], who previously served as the [[Chief Petty Officer of the Navy]], the most senior enlisted position in the Navy.
==Naval career== He joined the Navy in 1982 as a signalman. He was promoted to Chief Petty Officer 1st class in February 2005, serving with Maritime Force Atlantic Headquarters as Unit Chief before being appointed Coxswain of HMCS Ville de Qu√©bec in June 2006. Im 2008 he was appointed as Coxswain for Sea Training Atlantic.<ref name="NavyBio">{{cite web | url=http://www.navy-marine.forces.gc.ca/en/about/leadership-cpo-rcn.page | title=Chief Petty Officer of the Navy | publisher=Royal Canadian Navy | accessdate=November 4, 2015}}</ref>
In July 2009, he was appointed as the Formation Chief Petty Officer for Maritime Forces Atlantic, until he was appointed as Chief Petty Officer of the Navy in August 2012.<ref name="NavyBio" />
In August 2016 he relinquished the position of Chief Petty Officer of the Navy and was promoted Lieutenant Commander.<ref name="News2016">{{cite web | url=http://www.navy-marine.forces.gc.ca/en/news-operations/news-view.page?doc=new-command-chief-petty-officer-takes-over/isbkobpw | title=New Command Chief Petty Officer takes over | publisher=Royal Canadian Navy | date=August 18, 2016 | accessdate=September 12, 2016 | author=Blakeley, Darlene}}</ref>
==Honours and awards== He was appointed to the [[Order of Military Merit (Canada)|Order of Military Merit]] in January 2011.<ref name="appt">{{cite web | url=http://www.gg.ca/document.aspx?id=14007 | title=The Governor General Announces 114 new Appointments to the Order of Military Merit | publisher=Governor General of Canada | date=January 25, 2011 | accessdate=November 4, 2015}}</ref>
